Police union Sapu says the call centre staff's salaries were not increased from level 5 to level 7 as recommended by a task team two years ago. JOHANNESBURG Police Minister Fikile Mbalula says he will respond to the memorandum of demands given to him by the South African Police Union (Sapu) in 14 days.Employees in the police's 10111 call centre marched to the offices of the minister in Pretoria over salary disputes.Sapu's Oscar Skommerre says the call centre staff's salaries were not increased from level 5 to level 7 as recommended by a task team two years ago.The union threatened a complete shutdown should the department not answer favourably to their demands.The department's Vuyo Mhaga says, One of the things that we have to do is have an appreciation for why some of the recommendations that were made were not implemented and what were the hiccups, from there we will be in the right position to respond. 